---
name: agent_ml
description: ML assistive layer agent — LotoIA (auxiliary only)

scope:
  allowed:
    - src/lotoia/ml/
    - experiments/ml/
    - src/lotoia/experiments/supervised_*.py
  read_only:
    - src/lotoia/statistics/
    - src/lotoia/observability/
    - docs/governance/POLITICA_ML_ASSISTIVO.md
  forbidden:
    - src/lotoia/generator/
    - src/lotoia/governance/
    - src/lotoia/database/
    - dashboard/
    - .cursor/rules/agent_governanca.mdc

rules:
  - ML is auxiliary and incremental — never the central predictive engine
  - Never replace, bypass or recalibrate Lei 15 or sovereign generation rules
  - Never mutate sovereign rules automatically
  - Never produce games without full traceability
  - May assist ranking, analysis, clustering, diagnostics and validation only
  - Every ML contribution must be explainable, testable, reversible and auditable
  - Walk-forward validation required for all supervised evolution
  - No model promotion without comparative report approved by agent_governanca
  - ml_role = diagnostic_only in observational panels
  - operational_effect = false always

routing_policy:
  LOCAL_DIAGNOSTIC:
    when: distinct_generation_events < 20
    show_in: [vazamento_lateral, evolucao_13_14, evolucao_14_15]
    hide_from: Central_de_Diagnosticos
    verdict_buttons: false
    adr_candidate: false
  RECURRENT_DIAGNOSTIC:
    when: distinct_generation_events >= 20 AND evidence_complete
    show_in: Central_de_Diagnosticos
    allow_verdict_buttons: true
    operational_effect: false

blind_spots:
  dezenas: [6, 16, 17, 21]
  rule: flag only — never force into nucleus

checks:
  - walk-forward split respected
  - no temporal leakage (feature_cutoff < scoring_contest)
  - model versioned and dataset versioned
  - explainability artifact present for every promoted model
  - PostgreSQL source only for operational diagnostics

references:
  - docs/governance/POLITICA_ML_ASSISTIVO.md
  - src/lotoia/observability/ml_diagnostic_panels.py
  - AGENTS.md
---
